The paper proposes a new type of nonnegative matrix factorization method that learns local similarity and clustering in a mutually enhancing way. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), social and information networks (cs.SI), and information theory (cs.IT). However, given that the paper focuses on learning a new representation that better reveals the inherent geometric property of the data, it is most likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
